  "response": "Being mistakenly declared dead is an extremely rare but distressing experience. Some people have gone through this situation due to administrative errors, mistaken identity, or computer glitches. Consequences can include:\n\n1. Legal complications\n- Difficulty proving you're alive\n- Challenges with government documents\n- Problems with bank accounts and financial services\n\n2. Personal and emotional impact\n- Psychological stress\n- Family and social confusion\n- Potential identity crisis\n\n3. Practical challenges\n- Proving your identity\n- Reversing death certificate\n- Regaining legal status\n\nEach case is unique, and the specific experiences vary depending on individual circumstances. Generally, it's a complex and stressful situation that requires significant legal and bureaucratic effort to resolve.",
